      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BAREFOOT ZULU (4) won comfortably last time scoring by 5 lengths at Ballarat after jumping from box 5 (30.36). Has a tricky draw to overcome and will need a clean break. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. SILENT ASSASSIN (2) is racing well without winning, recording six minors on end, the latest hitting the ground running with a fast early sectional but finishing in the minors again when third (29.78) over 520m at this track. Comes through a solid form race last start. Well placed and gets his chance. ASTON RULER (1) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 488m at Mandurah two runs back then settled forward again when finishing third at Mandurah last start. Must be included in calculations. FROGS MONELLI (8) is a last start winner who rates one of the chances again.",
